History: Urosepsis, obstruction of the ureter, followup for interval changes.
Findings: AP chest radiograph was compared to prior study obtained at 6 pm. The day before. There is no change in the position of the right internal jugular line but there is interval progression of pulmonary edema. Bibasilar in particular left lower lobe consolidations are unchanged.
